## 🛠️ Strict Architecture & Integration Rules

### 1. Robust Counter API & Vercel KV (Redis)
- **Endpoint**: `/api/counter/route.ts` handles the processed playlists stats.
- **Hybrid Storage Design**:
  - **Production (Vercel KV)**: When environment variables `KV_REST_API_URL` and `KV_REST_API_TOKEN` are present, use `kv.incr('playlists_count')` and `kv.get('playlists_count')` for fast, atomic, persistent database storage.
  - **Local Fallback (stats.json)**: If KV variables are absent (local development), seamlessly fallback to reading/writing from `stats.json` in the root workspace. This ensures local dev requires no external setup.

### 2. GitHub API Rate-Limit Immunization (Very Important)
- **VPN / Shared IP Protection**: Anonymous requests to the GitHub Releases API (`api.github.com/repos/.../releases`) are heavily throttled.
- **No Infinite Loading / Broken Links**: 
  - Never display infinite loading state (`...`) for version tags. Default to the latest hardcoded version (`v1.9.1` or newer) in the initial state of components like [Hero.tsx](src/components/Hero.tsx).
  - Check `res.ok` before parsing JSON and throw on rate-limit HTTP errors.
  - Always pre-populate direct fallbacks in [DownloadButton.tsx](src/components/DownloadButton.tsx) with direct binary links for Windows (`.exe`), macOS (`.dmg`), and Linux (`.AppImage`) based on the latest stable version (e.g., `https://github.com/Gnzikoune/youtube-downloader/releases/download/v1.9.1/YT-Downloader-Pro-Setup-1.9.1.exe`). Clicking the download button must NEVER direct the user to the generic GitHub Releases page if the API fails.

### 3. Mobile Money Donations (SingPay API)
- **SingPay Push USSD Integration**: The route `/api/donate` communicates with the SingPay gateway.
- **Secrets Security**: The `SINGPAY_CLIENT_SECRET` must remain strictly server-side. Do NOT expose it in client-side Next.js routes.

### 4. Interactive UX & Navigation Rules
- **Smooth Scroll CTA**: The navbar logo and name "YT Downloader Pro" must link to `/#home` (smooth scrolling to the top). The navbar "Télécharger" CTA link must point to `/#download` (smooth scrolling to the final Download section at the bottom), keeping users engaged on the page instead of redirecting them away to GitHub.

---

## 🚀 Git Conventions
